1
00:00:03,150 --> 00:00:05,370
This is a world of magic.

2
00:00:06,860 --> 00:00:11,660
Magic is bought and sold here every day, and 
is an integral part of people's daily lives.

3
00:00:13,290 --> 00:00:17,460
Wizards, those who use magic 
in order to make a living,

4
00:00:17,460 --> 00:00:21,700
belong to various guilds, and 
perform jobs on commission.

5
00:00:22,920 --> 00:00:27,170
And in a certain city, 
there lies a certain guild.

6
00:00:28,090 --> 00:00:31,670
A guild from which various 
legends were once born...

7
00:00:31,670 --> 00:00:34,620
Or rather, will continue to be 
born long into the future...

8
00:00:35,370 --> 00:00:36,340
And its name is:

9
00:00:36,930 --> 00:00:38,490
Fairy Tail.

10
00:02:12,740 --> 00:02:15,540
Magnolia, during sakura season.

11
00:02:16,390 --> 00:02:19,020
And here is Fairy Tail.

12
00:02:20,550 --> 00:02:22,490
Listen up, everyone!

13
00:02:22,840 --> 00:02:26,490
Those who call themselves wizards shall 
ne'er neglect sharpening their skills!

14
00:02:26,680 --> 00:02:30,090
They shall polish their techniques, 
and perform jobs on request!

15
00:02:30,090 --> 00:02:33,020
And they must earn their daily bread!

16
00:02:33,020 --> 00:02:36,390
For as there be sunny days, 
surely there be rainy ones!

17
00:02:36,390 --> 00:02:39,280
For as there be days in which work 
is finished without trouble,

18
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:41,680
surely there be days which are 
naught but an uphill struggle!

19
00:02:42,080 --> 00:02:42,680
However!

20
00:02:43,250 --> 00:02:47,200
No matter what happens, 
tomorrow will always come!

21
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:51,100
And we shall continue to 
walk the path, as wizards!

22
00:02:51,680 --> 00:02:55,440
That's what it means to 
be a Fairy Tail wizard!

23
00:02:58,650 --> 00:03:02,160
Everyone, you've worked 
really hard this past year!

24
00:03:02,160 --> 00:03:05,570
And so, in honor of your hard work, 
tomorrow will be the long-awaited...

25
00:03:06,770 --> 00:03:10,030
...super-fun hanami party!

26
00:03:11,950 --> 00:03:13,860
And today we'll have a pre-celebration!

27
00:03:13,860 --> 00:03:15,300
Drink! Drink!

28
00:03:15,300 --> 00:03:16,360
This is messed up.

29
00:03:19,340 --> 00:03:20,610
Rainbow Sakura

30
00:03:23,280 --> 00:03:26,570
Everyone, please take it easy 
since tomorrow's the real deal.

31
00:03:28,420 --> 00:03:30,770
So everyone's saying "drink, drink" 
just 'cause it's hanami time?

32
00:03:30,770 --> 00:03:32,910
Isn't everyone getting a little too excited?

33
00:03:32,910 --> 00:03:35,000
You're one to talk.

34
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:37,910
It's like you're at a hanami all year!

35
00:03:37,910 --> 00:03:39,780
If you're a Man, then 
look at cherry blossoms!

36
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:43,610
Dad, I'm counting on you to win the 
grand prize at bingo this year!

37
00:03:44,160 --> 00:03:45,970
Sure! Leave it to me!

38
00:03:46,380 --> 00:03:47,950
Just watch me this year!

39
00:03:48,380 --> 00:03:51,150
It was no use last year 
or the one before that...

40
00:03:51,320 --> 00:03:53,660
Okay then... I'm gonna 
do my best at bingo, too!

41
00:03:54,070 --> 00:03:55,430
Uh, how's that work exactly?

42
00:03:55,740 --> 00:03:57,090
You know, guts and stuff.

43
00:03:57,670 --> 00:03:59,230
I don't get these people.

44
00:03:59,640 --> 00:04:01,960
Everyone's acting like their 
heads are in the clouds.

45
00:04:01,960 --> 00:04:03,650
It's just cherry blossom season, sheesh!

46
00:04:03,960 --> 00:04:06,680
The people making requests realize it.

47
00:04:07,900 --> 00:04:11,030
There aren't many requests since 
everyone knows that Fairy Tail's

48
00:04:11,030 --> 00:04:12,650
too busy partying to do much work.

49
00:04:13,340 --> 00:04:17,090
Give me a... Hey, how about 
you go on a job, huh?

50
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:20,450
What's the matter, Juvia?

51
00:04:21,850 --> 00:04:25,630
Gray-sama... Gray-sama went off on a job!

52
00:04:25,940 --> 00:04:29,540
Juvia can't believe how lonely the 
guild is without Gray-sama here!

53
00:04:30,530 --> 00:04:33,570
He can't help it, okay? 
He's a Fairy Tail wizard!

54
00:04:33,800 --> 00:04:35,000
Like you can say anything!

55
00:04:35,870 --> 00:04:39,090
But, Juvia's been left behind!

56
00:04:39,470 --> 00:04:43,130
Well, Gray's formed a team with Natsu and 
the others, so that's just how it is.

57
00:04:43,350 --> 00:04:47,350
But they took Wendy and Carla with them!

58
00:04:47,350 --> 00:04:50,170
It's so they can get used 
to our guild's jobs,

59
00:04:50,170 --> 00:04:52,180
since they just transferred 
from Cait Shelter.

60
00:04:52,530 --> 00:04:57,750
Juvia knows... Juvia knows... but she's sad!

61
00:05:04,480 --> 00:05:06,490
Gate of the Clock, I open thee!

62
00:05:07,670 --> 00:05:08,840
Horologium!

63
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:24,350
This is Mt. Hakobe.

64
00:05:26,470 --> 00:05:30,730
"I ended up here in light clothes 
again... It's too damn cold!"

65
00:05:30,730 --> 00:05:32,600
...she says.

66
00:05:33,100 --> 00:05:34,790
I-It is cold...

67
00:05:34,790 --> 00:05:37,480
Oh, come off it. This isn't bad. 
You're embarrassing yourself.

68
00:05:38,050 --> 00:05:40,580
"Wendy, come inside too! 
You'll catch a cold."

69
00:05:40,910 --> 00:05:42,610
...she says.

70
00:05:43,180 --> 00:05:46,240
Really? Then I'll take 
you up on that offer...

71
00:05:46,650 --> 00:05:47,650
How about you, Carla?

72
00:05:47,850 --> 00:05:49,190
I am perfectly fine, thank you.

73
00:05:49,700 --> 00:05:53,450
Personally, I think cold is something you 
can manage if you mentally prepare yourself.

74
00:05:54,060 --> 00:05:55,930
The weather seems to be clearing.

75
00:05:56,150 --> 00:05:59,600
I'm starving! Is there any fire 'round here?

76
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:01,190
It's warm in here!

77
00:06:01,880 --> 00:06:03,400
I wanna go home now!

78
00:06:03,630 --> 00:06:06,630
Crap... It's hard to walk 
when it's piled up this high.

79
00:06:06,980 --> 00:06:08,680
Put on some clothes first!

80
00:06:09,860 --> 00:06:14,130
Hey, Natsu... You think there really 
is an herb as useful as that?

81
00:06:14,400 --> 00:06:18,300
Who knows? The request bill said it 
was here, so it probably is, you know?

82
00:06:18,530 --> 00:06:22,420
But the part about how steeping it 
as a tea or baking it into a cake

83
00:06:22,420 --> 00:06:25,930
can temporarily magnify 
a wizard's magic power,

84
00:06:25,930 --> 00:06:28,360
I think that's just a bunch of malarkey.

85
00:06:28,590 --> 00:06:31,800
You know what they say: there's 
always a tasty fish to catch!

86
00:06:32,130 --> 00:06:34,620
You mean to say "there's always a catch".

87
00:06:35,780 --> 00:06:37,540
Erza corrected me!

88
00:06:37,540 --> 00:06:41,610
Whether or not it is effective, the request 
was to gather the herb from this mountain.

89
00:06:42,270 --> 00:06:45,400
And if we gather quite a lot, we can 
use it as a prize for tomorrow's bingo.

90
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:47,040
Everyone will be pleased.

91
00:06:47,440 --> 00:06:50,770
Hey, herbs! If you're out 
there, say somethin'!

92
00:06:50,770 --> 00:06:52,150
As if, dolt.

93
00:06:52,150 --> 00:06:53,390
What'd you say!?

94
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:57,350
Don't just say whatever pops into your head!

95
00:06:57,680 --> 00:07:00,690
And I don't even know what the 
hell you're saying, idiot!

96
00:07:02,450 --> 00:07:05,280
You're gonna get it, Prince Frostbite Boxers!

97
00:07:05,280 --> 00:07:08,610
Shut the hell up, you whiny little flicker!

98
00:07:08,610 --> 00:07:10,210
Stop this!

99
00:07:11,460 --> 00:07:13,860
I wish we could hurry this 
job up and go home...

100
00:07:14,240 --> 00:07:16,320
I want to get ready for the hanami tomorrow.

101
00:07:16,320 --> 00:07:18,450
I'm really looking forward to it, myself!

102
00:07:18,790 --> 00:07:22,050
The sakura in Magnolia are really beautiful!

103
00:07:22,050 --> 00:07:25,510
And what's more, at nighttime the cherry 
blossoms become rainbow-colored!

104
00:07:25,900 --> 00:07:28,420
They're just super-beautiful!

105
00:07:28,870 --> 00:07:30,730
Rainbow-colored sakura?

106
00:07:30,730 --> 00:07:33,350
It's even beautiful imagining it!

107
00:07:33,350 --> 00:07:34,610
You know?

108
00:07:34,610 --> 00:07:36,510
...she says.

109
00:07:37,390 --> 00:07:40,850
And then, you know... Everyone 
makes and brings lunch,

110
00:07:40,850 --> 00:07:44,770
and beneath the rainbow sakura 
they stare up all day long,

111
00:07:44,770 --> 00:07:47,130
and everyone livens it up for a grand hanami!

112
00:07:47,130 --> 00:07:49,700
Man, I can't wait until tomorrow!

113
00:07:49,700 --> 00:07:53,550
That's why I want to hurry up and 
finish this job, get back to Magnolia,

114
00:07:53,550 --> 00:07:57,660
and then, and then bake cookies... and then, 
and then choose the clothes I'll wear....

115
00:07:57,660 --> 00:08:00,540
And then, and then I'll go straight 
to bed without writing my novel...

116
00:08:00,540 --> 00:08:02,800
And then, and then I'll do 
my hair up nice and cute...

117
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:03,840
And then, and then...

118
00:08:03,840 --> 00:08:04,370
Huh?

119
00:08:06,050 --> 00:08:09,230
Lucy-san, did you go to the hanami last year?

120
00:08:09,980 --> 00:08:11,000
Uh...

121
00:08:11,210 --> 00:08:16,580
I was pretty sure I heard that it hasn't 
been a year since you joined the guild...

122
00:08:17,090 --> 00:08:19,390
Oh, yeah... I guess this is my first time.

123
00:08:23,450 --> 00:08:27,140
I think I dreamed I was there 
from being too excited about it!

124
00:08:28,360 --> 00:08:32,510
It really does sound like a blast. 
I can't wait for it, either!

125
00:08:33,010 --> 00:08:36,340
It'll be so exciting to look at the cherry 
blossoms with everyone else from the guild.

126
00:08:36,340 --> 00:08:39,370
Yeah, for sure! Let's enjoy them 
together, as fellow first-timers!

127
00:08:40,500 --> 00:08:43,030
It is time. Fare thee well!

128
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:46,640
So cooooold!

129
00:08:46,750 --> 00:08:47,860
Oh, jeez...

130
00:08:48,290 --> 00:08:50,130
You two should go search now!

131
00:08:50,410 --> 00:08:51,970
But...

132
00:08:54,440 --> 00:08:57,590
I can smell it! That's 
definitely the smell of herbs.

133
00:08:57,900 --> 00:09:00,150
Just as good a nose as usual.

134
00:09:00,150 --> 00:09:04,150
Wait... Have you ever 
smelled these herbs before?

135
00:09:04,150 --> 00:09:07,220
Nope. Never smelled 'em, but I'm sure.

136
00:09:07,440 --> 00:09:09,110
Let's go, Happy!

137
00:09:09,110 --> 00:09:10,540
Aye, sir!

138
00:09:10,930 --> 00:09:12,350
H-Hey!

139
00:09:12,950 --> 00:09:15,420
Man, who lit his butt on fire?

140
00:09:15,420 --> 00:09:17,600
Anyway, let's follow him.

141
00:09:17,600 --> 00:09:19,780
His nose is nothing to sneeze at.

142
00:09:20,230 --> 00:09:24,230
Maybe it's my imagination, but I have 
a <i>really</i> bad feeling about this.

143
00:09:24,230 --> 00:09:26,910
Your instincts are usually correct, Carla.

144
00:09:34,490 --> 00:09:34,950
That was fast.

145
00:09:35,300 --> 00:09:37,200
Fast is good.

146
00:09:37,200 --> 00:09:38,310
Impressive, as always.

147
00:09:38,310 --> 00:09:39,730
Natsu-san, wow!

148
00:09:39,730 --> 00:09:41,150
Yup, he's a beast.

149
00:09:41,930 --> 00:09:44,510
Right then. Let's pick these and get home.

150
00:09:44,510 --> 00:09:45,860
Aye, sir!

151
00:09:49,200 --> 00:09:52,630
A Blizzardvern. Also known as a White Wyvern.

152
00:09:53,150 --> 00:09:56,480
A monster that lives on Mt. Hakobe.

153
00:09:56,840 --> 00:09:59,930
Contrary to its appearance, it's herbivorous.

154
00:10:00,480 --> 00:10:04,320
By the way, its favorite food is these herbs.

155
00:10:04,320 --> 00:10:05,400
What?!

156
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:07,310
You wanna keep 'em all to yourself?!

157
00:10:11,270 --> 00:10:15,340
What a nice break. We can kill 
two birds with one stone.

158
00:10:15,800 --> 00:10:19,680
You know that the scales of a White 
Wyvern sell for a pretty penny?

159
00:10:19,680 --> 00:10:23,760
All right then! After we get those 
herbs, we'll strip all its scales off!

160
00:10:24,420 --> 00:10:27,410
Leave this to us. Lucy, Wendy, stand back!

161
00:10:28,440 --> 00:10:29,850
I'll fight, too!

162
00:10:31,410 --> 00:10:31,860
Requip!

163
00:10:34,850 --> 00:10:38,400
We'll draw its attention. 
While it's distracted,

164
00:10:38,400 --> 00:10:40,300
you all go and gather the herbs!

165
00:10:40,600 --> 00:10:41,200
Right!

166
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:42,580
I suppose so.

167
00:10:42,890 --> 00:10:46,040
Wait... Isn't this the 
most dangerous job of all?

168
00:10:46,320 --> 00:10:47,700
I'm counting on you!

169
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:49,760
Right! We'll do it, gladly!

170
00:10:49,760 --> 00:10:51,550
Here we go, Natsu, Gray!

171
00:10:55,720 --> 00:10:57,270
Hurry, hurry!

172
00:10:57,270 --> 00:10:59,010
Don't sound like such a wimp!

173
00:10:59,560 --> 00:11:01,970
Dazzling Blaze of the Fire Dragon!

174
00:11:06,400 --> 00:11:07,790
Natsu-san's flames...

175
00:11:07,790 --> 00:11:09,540
...are being reflected by the air pressure!

176
00:11:11,750 --> 00:11:14,250
Ice Make Saucer!

177
00:11:16,850 --> 00:11:18,170
How about this?

178
00:11:19,250 --> 00:11:20,170
Hey, whoa there...

179
00:11:20,170 --> 00:11:20,990
Wait, you!

180
00:11:22,820 --> 00:11:24,880
Fools! You should have dodged!

181
00:11:24,880 --> 00:11:26,550
Uh, how about a little, you know...

182
00:11:26,550 --> 00:11:28,160
Apologize first, damn it...

183
00:11:31,550 --> 00:11:33,500
This thing's more powerful than we thought!

184
00:11:33,990 --> 00:11:34,730
Everyone...

185
00:11:35,410 --> 00:11:38,300
Okay, then... I'm not gonna lose, either!

186
00:11:42,800 --> 00:11:44,890
Natsu, Erza, now!

187
00:11:45,950 --> 00:11:46,570
Leave it to us!

188
00:11:49,640 --> 00:11:51,940
Iron Fist of the Fire Dragon!

189
00:11:53,300 --> 00:11:54,800
Got it!

190
00:11:54,800 --> 00:11:59,380
Look at me! See? I'm one of the members 
of Fairy Tail's strongest team!

191
00:12:01,580 --> 00:12:03,280
Avalanche!

192
00:12:11,430 --> 00:12:12,310
Is everyone safe?

193
00:12:13,410 --> 00:12:16,130
Well, that's what we get for 
making all that commotion.

194
00:12:16,650 --> 00:12:18,000
Yup, they're beasts...

195
00:12:18,570 --> 00:12:20,190
Huh? Where's Lucy-san?

196
00:12:20,450 --> 00:12:22,250
Lucy, where are you?

197
00:12:26,590 --> 00:12:27,340
Cold...

198
00:12:34,660 --> 00:12:37,150
Today is the day of the hanami.

199
00:12:43,130 --> 00:12:44,980
You aren't coming, Lucy?

200
00:12:45,190 --> 00:12:47,660
The cherry blossoms in Magnolia 
are pretty, you know!

201
00:12:48,180 --> 00:12:49,670
I-I really wanna go...

202
00:12:53,210 --> 00:12:55,210
I was really looking forward to it...

203
00:12:55,210 --> 00:12:57,120
Are you okay, Lucy?

204
00:12:58,280 --> 00:13:00,060
Can't you tell just by looking at me?

205
00:13:00,990 --> 00:13:02,500
I've caught a cold...

206
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:07,650
Sorry... I'm going to sleep...

207
00:13:08,840 --> 00:13:10,050
Take care of yourself.

208
00:13:12,820 --> 00:13:15,100
Man, that sucks.

209
00:13:15,320 --> 00:13:19,100
It's too bad she caught a cold, after 
she was looking forward to it so much.

210
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:24,000
Hanami?! I'm there! I'm sooo there!

211
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:26,400
What should I wear?

212
00:13:26,400 --> 00:13:28,170
I know! I'll bake cookies!

213
00:13:28,170 --> 00:13:29,600
And then, and then...

214
00:13:29,600 --> 00:13:33,250
That's right. This will be the 
first hanami for Lucy, won't it?

215
00:13:33,540 --> 00:13:34,440
A Man!

216
00:13:34,640 --> 00:13:35,550
Hanami?

217
00:13:35,550 --> 00:13:39,440
Hanami is where everyone drinks and eats and 
has a party while looking at the sakura blossoms.

218
00:13:39,930 --> 00:13:41,210
You're makin' too much of a fuss about it.

219
00:13:41,500 --> 00:13:45,520
But Magnolia has those rainbow sakura that 
are supposed to be really beautiful, right?

220
00:13:45,840 --> 00:13:50,690
When I came to Magnolia, I totally 
couldn't wait to go see them!

221
00:13:51,750 --> 00:13:53,700
Poor thing...

222
00:13:53,700 --> 00:13:55,500
I feel bad for Lucy.

223
00:14:02,950 --> 00:14:05,320
Now everyone, eat up all you want!

224
00:14:05,520 --> 00:14:07,410
This here's mine!

225
00:14:07,410 --> 00:14:09,340
You brought your own barrel?

226
00:14:09,340 --> 00:14:11,210
No one's gonna take it, sheesh.

227
00:14:11,690 --> 00:14:14,040
Hanami is Man!

228
00:14:14,040 --> 00:14:15,590
I don't get what that means.

229
00:14:15,590 --> 00:14:16,890
Levy, want something to eat?

230
00:14:16,890 --> 00:14:18,080
Levy, want something to drink?

231
00:14:18,580 --> 00:14:20,580
Huh? She caught a cold?

232
00:14:20,580 --> 00:14:21,930
Is it serious?

233
00:14:22,290 --> 00:14:23,220
Yeah...

234
00:14:23,220 --> 00:14:26,610
Her nose is all runny, and 
her face is flushed...

235
00:14:26,610 --> 00:14:28,130
Why'd she catch a cold?

236
00:14:28,130 --> 00:14:29,610
You don't get it, do you?

237
00:14:30,060 --> 00:14:32,990
Even though Lucy-san was looking 
forward to it so much...

238
00:14:32,990 --> 00:14:37,040
Oh, that's right! Why don't you 
cure her with your magic, Wendy?

239
00:14:37,340 --> 00:14:41,310
I already cast the spell. She'll 
be fine again by tomorrow, but...

240
00:14:42,280 --> 00:14:43,540
Tomorrow, huh?

241
00:14:49,270 --> 00:14:50,350
Hanami...

242
00:14:51,260 --> 00:14:53,900
I bet everyone's having a lot of fun now...

243
00:14:54,690 --> 00:14:56,580
I sure wish I could have gone...

244
00:14:59,940 --> 00:15:04,750
And now, we'll begin the traditional 
hanami bingo tournament!

245
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:07,740
Bingo!

246
00:15:09,450 --> 00:15:12,010
We've got a bunch of high 
quality prizes again this year!

247
00:15:12,200 --> 00:15:14,260
Everyone, give it everything you got!

248
00:15:17,150 --> 00:15:19,000
Everyone ready?

249
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:20,650
Aye, sir!

250
00:15:20,650 --> 00:15:23,320
Then, please punch out the center circle!

251
00:15:23,920 --> 00:15:25,600
I'm gonna get the top prize, for sure!

252
00:15:25,600 --> 00:15:26,770
Do your best, Dad!

253
00:15:27,290 --> 00:15:28,320
Let's bingo!

254
00:15:28,580 --> 00:15:30,450
The first number is...

255
00:15:35,090 --> 00:15:36,220
24!

256
00:15:36,550 --> 00:15:38,550
All right! Right off the bat.

257
00:15:38,550 --> 00:15:40,100
What incredible luck...

258
00:15:40,100 --> 00:15:41,500
Levy, you can do it!

259
00:15:48,390 --> 00:15:52,180
Now that I think about it, it 
hasn't even been a year, has it?

260
00:15:54,700 --> 00:15:58,850
I ran away from home, trying to 
join Fairy Tail, my dream guild...

261
00:15:59,300 --> 00:16:00,770
And that's how I met Natsu.

262
00:16:01,520 --> 00:16:03,190
Then, I joined the guild.

263
00:16:04,550 --> 00:16:06,520
After that, time just flew...

264
00:16:07,900 --> 00:16:09,110
Next is 5!

265
00:16:10,330 --> 00:16:12,450
Yes! Got it! Man!

266
00:16:12,450 --> 00:16:14,270
Being a man has nothing to do with it.

267
00:16:14,270 --> 00:16:15,670
I'm getting nothing here...

268
00:16:16,100 --> 00:16:18,090
Natsu, you don't want to play bingo?

269
00:16:18,090 --> 00:16:18,840
Naw...

270
00:16:20,030 --> 00:16:25,420
In just a short time, there's been 
so much over-the-top stuff...

271
00:16:45,520 --> 00:16:46,750
68!

272
00:16:47,100 --> 00:16:48,290
Bingo!

273
00:16:48,550 --> 00:16:49,230
Seriously?

274
00:16:49,520 --> 00:16:50,900
Look at her go...

275
00:16:50,900 --> 00:16:52,530
I'm just one away from 3 different bingos!

276
00:16:51,900 --> 00:16:53,420
Erza, you're the first bingo!

277
00:16:53,800 --> 00:16:55,900
Even luck can come from training!

278
00:16:56,200 --> 00:16:58,200
S-So, w-what's the prize?

279
00:16:58,200 --> 00:16:59,750
Right! Here.

280
00:16:59,970 --> 00:17:03,620
It's the herbs that are rumored to 
temporarily increase one's magic power!

281
00:17:03,950 --> 00:17:05,300
What?!

282
00:17:05,800 --> 00:17:07,610
Those are the herbs we picked!

283
00:17:07,940 --> 00:17:09,800
And they're already dried up!

284
00:17:10,650 --> 00:17:13,890
Probably 'cause we took them 
suddenly to a warm climate.

285
00:17:14,270 --> 00:17:16,800
My bingo...

286
00:17:16,800 --> 00:17:17,620
Now, now...

287
00:17:19,410 --> 00:17:23,590
A whole lot happened, that's for sure...

288
00:17:38,450 --> 00:17:42,050
And in my way, I think I've 
done my best to deal with it...

289
00:17:42,050 --> 00:17:42,740
Yeah...

290
00:17:43,080 --> 00:17:44,280
Bingo!

291
00:17:44,280 --> 00:17:46,510
Seriously?! I ain't even got one hit yet!

292
00:17:46,750 --> 00:17:48,600
That's 'cause your skills are rusty!

293
00:17:48,600 --> 00:17:49,830
Dad, you can do it!

294
00:17:50,150 --> 00:17:52,080
I have a feeling there's no way I'll win.

295
00:17:52,380 --> 00:17:54,800
Your intuition is usually correct, Carla...

296
00:17:56,350 --> 00:17:58,990
The prizes are gonna be gone soon.

297
00:17:58,990 --> 00:18:02,140
I was hoping to at least 
bring Lucy a present...

298
00:18:04,560 --> 00:18:05,730
115!

299
00:18:06,210 --> 00:18:07,600
Bingo!

300
00:18:08,200 --> 00:18:08,860
Huh?

301
00:18:08,860 --> 00:18:09,800
Oh, my...

302
00:18:09,800 --> 00:18:11,190
Three at the same time?

303
00:18:11,550 --> 00:18:15,630
Then I'll give the prize to whoever makes 
me laugh the most with a single gag.

304
00:18:15,630 --> 00:18:16,860
A single gag?!

305
00:18:16,860 --> 00:18:22,160
The prize is a pair of tickets to a fancy 
hotel at Akane Resort for 3 days and 2 nights!

306
00:18:22,450 --> 00:18:23,300
Whoa!

307
00:18:23,300 --> 00:18:24,730
A vacation for two?!

308
00:18:25,180 --> 00:18:28,760
Akane Resort, huh? I'll give 
it as a present to my sister!

309
00:18:28,760 --> 00:18:32,080
Together with Gray-sama 
for 3 days and 2 nights?

310
00:18:32,080 --> 00:18:34,210
Juvia's heart isn't ready for such...

311
00:18:35,600 --> 00:18:36,620
A single gag.

312
00:18:37,070 --> 00:18:39,940
Truly a one-shot battle on the edge.

313
00:18:41,170 --> 00:18:43,930
And that means it's my turn, partner.

314
00:18:44,230 --> 00:18:45,690
You again?!

315
00:18:45,690 --> 00:18:48,930
Get outta here! You ain't 
even close to a bingo!

316
00:18:49,230 --> 00:18:50,200
Natsu...

317
00:18:50,340 --> 00:18:50,840
Yeah?

318
00:19:00,390 --> 00:19:02,790
It seemed my heart would break 
countless numbers of times...

319
00:19:03,410 --> 00:19:05,100
We got into some crazy trouble...

320
00:19:05,630 --> 00:19:07,910
There were enemies more powerful 
than I could have ever imagined...

321
00:19:09,700 --> 00:19:14,870
But because he and everyone in the 
guild were always there for me...

322
00:19:16,350 --> 00:19:20,390
Crying... laughing... and everything else...

323
00:19:26,120 --> 00:19:29,420
Well, a whole lot happened, that's for sure.

324
00:19:39,670 --> 00:19:42,110
But I'm sure that's it.

325
00:19:43,510 --> 00:19:48,110
Though everyone holds their 
own tough times inside them...

326
00:20:08,750 --> 00:20:12,500
Even so, everyone is trying to 
move forward, I'm sure of it.

327
00:20:12,860 --> 00:20:15,500
That's what Fairy Tail is.

328
00:20:21,750 --> 00:20:25,480
I've really joined a great place here.

329
00:20:29,800 --> 00:20:30,620
Time to sleep.

330
00:20:47,450 --> 00:20:50,610
What's this? It's noisy outside...

331
00:21:11,040 --> 00:21:12,800
What is this?

332
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:38,900
How beautiful...

333
00:21:46,020 --> 00:21:47,620
So, cold all better?

334
00:21:48,720 --> 00:21:50,290
Yup! Good as new!

335
00:21:50,290 --> 00:21:52,160
Good for you, Lucy!

336
00:21:52,550 --> 00:21:56,940
Hey! Which one o' you dug up one of the 
city's precious sakura trees, huh?!

337
00:21:56,940 --> 00:21:59,990
The Mayor is seriously pissed!

338
00:22:04,340 --> 00:22:05,890
Man, what an idiot.

339
00:22:05,890 --> 00:22:07,640
Gray-sama, your clothes...

340
00:22:08,270 --> 00:22:09,590
This is messed up.

341
00:22:10,070 --> 00:22:11,140
Thanks!

342
00:22:12,570 --> 00:22:14,090
W-What are you talkin' about?

343
00:22:14,090 --> 00:22:16,850
Did we do something? I don't think so.

344
00:23:55,940 --> 00:23:57,510
Thank you very much!

345
00:23:57,510 --> 00:23:59,090
What was that for?

346
00:23:59,090 --> 00:24:00,870
Something just flashed across my mind.

347
00:24:00,870 --> 00:24:02,800
What's it called again? A...

348
00:24:02,800 --> 00:24:03,670
Kaleidoscope?

349
00:24:03,670 --> 00:24:04,880
Huh?!

350
00:24:04,880 --> 00:24:07,420
No, it's like, a premonition.

351
00:24:07,580 --> 00:24:09,700
Huh? Premonition of what?

352
00:24:09,700 --> 00:24:13,410
I have a feeling that something bad 
might happen...or it might not...

353
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:16,890
Next time: Wendy's first big job!

354
00:24:17,250 --> 00:24:20,270
What was it? I'm sure I've 
heard that line before...

355
00:24:20,270 --> 00:24:22,130
Thank you very much!

356
00:24:22,130 --> 00:24:23,670
Wait, Happy... You too?!

357
00:24:23,670 --> 00:24:25,670


